    <p>MEX­ICO CITY • Af­ter the dis­ap­point­ment of see­ing the Mex­i­can Formula One Grand Prix can­celled this year due to the coro­n­avirus pan­demic, the Mex­ico City gov­ern­ment has turned its track into a drive-in cin­ema.</p>
    <p>Peo­ple can now drive up to Turn Four of the Au­to­dromo Her­manos Ro­driguez in Mex­ico City, which has been tem­po­rar­ily con­verted into the Au­tocin­ema Mix­huca, which can hold up to 415 ve­hi­cles.</p>


